name: Air Canada Express Embraer 175 Landing at Washington Reagan Airport (DCA) ᴴᴰ
description:
D.C. is a beautiful city! Here we have my view on board Air Canada Express flight 7616 from Toronto-Pearson landing at Washington Ronald Reagan National Airport, unfortunately on runway 01 as I was really hoping to experience the River Visual approach. Nonetheless, it's still a beautiful view of the city as we follow the Potomac before make a firm landing and a very short rollout on runway 01 at DCA. Enjoy this comprehensive arrival footage!

Thanks for watching!

-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-=-

VIDEO LOG:
02:00 - Banking for right downwind for runway 01.  
03:14 - Flying by Joint Base Andrews on downwind.
03:30 - Spoilers extended.
04:05 - Flaps begin extending.
05:25 - Turning base.
09:30 - Flaps extended fully.
10:45 - Short final.
11:05 - Touchdown! 
11:35 - Vacating the runway.
